description: this is a winter project, parts or whatever you would like. Selling a 20 ft Stingray with an I/O and the 350 chevy.  boat has thru the hull exhaust and sounded great when it was running.  Selling because i just am not using it as much any more and have been going out on my friends boats. Did not get taken out at all this year.  boat was running about 50 and feels pretty good in the water but I think with the right engine in it it should be able to do in the 60's. It will need an engine. oil pressure is  low and was getting lower each time i took it out but there are no knocks. last time i tried to start the boat a couple of months ago would not start.  will need a carb rebuild or a new carburator. I got this from a buddy just after he blew up the previous engine.  he had a block laying around and threw the engine together that is currently in it.  the engine does have edelbrock aluminum heads on it not sure which ones. out drive would become hard to shift after you were out for a little bit, when i would get home i would open the drain screw and some water would come out, so i think a seal was bad and it was creating too much pressure in the lower end to allow easy shifting. It will not come with a battery. interior is in need of attention as you can see in the pics.  the trailer does have good tires on it and goes down the road fine.any questions please feel free to ask and thanks for looking.  if you are not able to fix this yourself this is probably not the boat for you. i feel boats like this in good condition will sell for about 5k or better. stainless prop and life jackets are not included with the boat. if this add is still here the boat is still for sale
title: 1990 STINGRAY MAXIM PROJECT
